<string name="help_content"><![CDATA[
<h1>PassAndroid</h1>

Keep boarding passes, train tickets, event tickets, coupons and loyalty cards in one place.
Once a pass is imported, it stays available <b>offline</b>.

<h1>How to use it</h1>
<ol>
<li>Open a <b>.pkpass</b> or <b>.espass</b> file from your browser, email or file manager.</li>
<li>Import the pass once.</li>
<li>Use the barcode, details and attachments later without a network connection.</li>
</ol>

<h1>Useful while travelling</h1>
<ul>
<li>Fast offline access to the barcode</li>
<li>Readable trip details and times</li>
<li>Quick links to maps and calendar when the pass provides them</li>
<li>No account required</li>
</ul>

<h1>Sample passes</h1>
Need something to test with? <a href=\'http://espass.it/examples/\'>Open example passes</a>.

<h1>Feedback</h1>
Send feedback by email <a href=\'mailto:ligi@ligi.de\'>to the author</a> or visit the project page on GitHub.

<h1>Legal</h1>
<p>This app is not affiliated with Apple - Passbook might be trademarked by Apple, but it\'s introduced like a standard so this should be okay.</p>
